Lost Inside the Pair Somewhere

Gazing upon me, a pair unlike 
others, centered by complete
honestly wrapped by a ring of
love, circumvent to a white
nothingness so pure and 
reassuring that the frozen soul 
within me was softened.
Lashes of lace periodically
flickered lightly, protecting
the vulnerable treasures.
Scared and lost deep in the 
honesty, departing, I left my 
open heart in the ring and 
faded into the nothingness,
never to be found again.
The lashes dismissed the 
worries, and a single tear
temporarily flushed the pain
away.
Upon the fair was left a 
signature, displaying grief
and longing, ever submissive
to the suffering, of a lost lover
somewhere in the nothingness.
SIGNEND
